The manager was killed last month when suspects tried to force entry into the restaurant while staff were cashing up. JOHANNESBURG Police have confirmed the arrest of two suspects involved in the killing of the manager of the Sakhumzi restaurant in Vilakazi Street in Soweto on Tuesday. The manager was killed last month when suspects tried to force entry into the restaurant while staff were cashing up.Police say they are still investigating other possible suspects who could be behind the murder. The police's Kay Makhubele says the arrested suspects face charges of murder and armed robbery. One suspect was arrested in KwaZulu-Natal and another was arrested in Soweto. The weapons used in the crime were recovered and the suspects will appear before the Orlando Magistrates Court tomorrow. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)